title: For Sale:  AR-15, Ammo, Extras
postcontent:
This is a one-owner rifle, and I have maintained it meticulously.  I bought it because it was similar to my work gun so that I could train.  However, I got a lot less hooah, and I figured out that I'd rather not train in my off time.  So, I decided to turn it into a varmint/hunting rifle. 
When I initially bought it, it had a quadrail.  It was shooting 3+'' groups at 100 yards.  After the changes, I have it dialed in to 1.5'' or better groups at 100 yards…  Pretty good for a semi-automatic.  Obviously as you shoot, the groups are going to open up because of the heat, but the first five are usually within a quarter-sized diameter.  If you're taking more than 5 shots at an animal, you're either too far away or you suck.  I've shot about 300 rounds, give or take 100.  It has never had any steel cased ammo run through it, only the Aguila and Fusion rounds included in this sale.  The difference between the Agula FMJ and the Fusion rounds' point of impact is negligible at 100 yards. 
I'd recommend getting a solid zero with the Aguila, then confirm and/or adjust for the Fusion after that.  Seriously, I've found the sweet spot here for practice and hunting interchangeability.  Just give the rifle and barrel plenty of time to cool off.  Bonus, you can just unscrew the handguard to help it cool!  The vinyl tape on the handguard is so that it doesn’t resonate when it taps something else metal.  It can come off pretty easy.
Seriously, this is a very good set up as is…  If you want to fuck it up and make it look tacticool again, you get all the parts and tools necessary to ruin it again.
 The Rifle: AeroPrecision lower receiver Rock River Arms upper receiver 1 in 9 twist barrel Magpul CTR Carbine Stock (Milspec) Magpul Enhanced Aluminum Trigger Guard RRA Pistol Grip Yankee Hill Machine Low-Profile gas block Guntec USA 12'' free floating handguard Custom Muzzle Brakes Tactical Low Concussion Linear Muzzle Brake  The Glass: Vortex Crossfire II 2-7x32mm with the Dead Hold BDC Reticle Vortex rings  Ammo: 350 (by weight) Aguila 55gr FMJ  60 Fusion 62gr hunting rounds  Extras Not on the Rifle: 7'' quad rail Gas block with rail Front sight Rear Magpul MBUS sight A gnarly muzzle brake that is mean to your neighbors at the range Magpul Rail Vertical Grip Sightmark EOTech/magnifier combo knockoffAt least 3 magazinesI think you'd be hard pressed to find a better package for the price I'm asking.

title: For Sale:  UNICA 6 .357 MAGNUM -- 'AUTO-REVOLVER'...Quite Unusual & Scarce!
postcontent: This is a Mateba Model "Unica 6" AUTO-REVOLVER!! That's right, a semi-automatic revolver! Chambered for the .357 Magnum, this handgun is unlike anything else. It is designed so that the recoil of the fired shot rotates the cylinder and automatically cocks the hammer. Also unusual, the barrel is centered low to line up with the chamber at the bottom of the cylinder. It wears a 6-inch vent-rib barrel. There are even ambidextrous cylinder release levers (the full length left side lever is in the accessory pack). Overall condition is excellent, as new, This gun has not been shot much. The blue finish rates 99% overall. There is no rust or pitting. The one-piece walnut grip is in excellent shape without wear. The mechanics appear to be in good working order and the bore is excellent. It comes in the original plastic box with cardboard sleeve which is numbered to the gun. Also included is the instruction manual, parts diagram, and the unopened tool/accessory pack. It even has a "lucky serial number"...000777! Very unorthodox and highly collectible...trust me, you'll raise a few eyebrows at the range with this one!

title: For Sale:  Remington Versa Max
postcontent: The Remington® VERSA MAX® Semi-Auto Shotgun uses the VersaPort™ gas operation system that vents gas from the shotgun's chamber to operate the action. It is a very simple system with few moving parts and no O-rings, gaskets, or seals to maintain. The system uses the length of the shotgun shell hull to regulate the amount of gas, allowing the gun to operate with every type of shotgun shell from light 2-3/4" loads up to 3-1/2" magnums without any shooter adjustments. The versatility of the rugged, value-priced VERSA MAX Sportsman makes it equally well suited for turkey and waterfowl hunting with magnum loads, as well as upland birds, and even pass shooting doves with light field loads. The VERSA MAX Sportsman semi-automatic shotgun has a weather resistant, black synthetic stock with textured panels on the fore-end and pistol grip that provide a solid hold in any environment. The barrel and receiver are finished in a non-reflective matte black that enhances concealment in most hunting environments. A molded in sling swivel stud on the butt-stock and a stud on the magazine cap allow the quick attachment of a sling. The self-cleaning, gas operation system of the Remington VERSA MAX Semi-Auto shotgun reduces recoil considerably, allowing the shooter to follow-up on missed birds or shoot multiple targets quickly.
